  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">They are too quiet about Migration: Strengthening the Capacity of the Government of South Africa and Civil Society to Respond to the Needs of Vulnerable Migrants Living with Disability Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to strengthen the capacity of the government of South Africa and civil society to address the needs and rights of vulnerable migrants living with disability. This will be through sensitising policy makers on the plight of vulnerable Migrants Living with Disabilities (MLwD), and the nature of migration and disability, increasing the understanding of migration and disability through capacity building efforts, increasing advocacy for policy amendment and implementation as well as raising awareness about the needs and rights of MLwD.  Through working with stakeholders from civil society the project will strengthen their ability to respond to the need of MLwD, collecting quality data and advocacy efforts.</narrative>
  </description>
